				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Currently I update my sound engine in my vblank handler, after it's done with any necessary VRAM access. This works great for keeping the music going at a steady pace - as long as the screen's on. When I do turn off the screen (for a large transfer of data to VRAM, generally), there's inevitably a slight hiccup in the music as the tempo's thrown off.
<br />
<br />I'm considering moving sound updates to a timer interrupt handler, but my impression was that this wasn't done all that often. Is that the case? And if so, why/why not?
<br />
<br />Is there any particular approach that I should be taking?</div>

