					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Bugs Bunny's Crazy Castle 2 has this same thing; the music has a slight hiccup whenever a level starts, since the game disables the LCD controller to fill the pattern tables. It didn't take away from the game or anything, so I don't think most people would mind.
<br />
<br />And yes, the timer interrupt is actually quite commonly used for music engines. Donkey Kong 94 used it, and tons of Konami games used it.</div>

					
